  • Method Details

    • buildBulkInsertSelect

      protected final void buildBulkInsertSelect(Object builder, List<Object> objects)
      Description copied from class: BulkInsertWorkQueueBase
      Builds the insert select statement to find the objects that need work done and then create the appropriate work items. Subclasses should:
      • Narrow down the select statement to select just the target items that need work done
      • Use mapColumn to populate any work item columns that need to be set
      The delegate work item columns ProcessHistory and CreationTime are already populated when this method is called; nearly all subclasses should leave them alone.
      Specified by:
      buildBulkInsertSelect in class BulkInsertWorkQueueBase<T extends KeyableBean,StandardWorkItem>
      Parameters:
      builder - an insert select builder, which selects from a target type and inserts work items of work item type. The builder initially has no restrictions on its select statement so that it will return every instance of the target type.
      objects - the arguments passed to the batch process constructor

    • findTargets

      public final Iterator<T> findTargets()
      Description copied from class: WorkQueueBase
      This will return the items to be added to the work queue. IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: This needs to be implemented if you want to populate the work queue via it's batch process. This could be a simple query result if the determination is too complex, as the shouldProcessItem method can be used to fine tune these results. Once this has been defined you can add categories to the BatchProcessType to indicate that it is UIRunnable and/or Schedulable
      Specified by:
      findTargets in interface com.guidewire.pl.system.workqueue.WorkQueueTargetFinder<T extends KeyableBean>
      Overrides:
      findTargets in class WorkQueueBase<T extends KeyableBean,StandardWorkItem>
      Returns:
      an iterator over target items.
